      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "This week, Jeremi and Zachary are joined by Dr. Peniel Joseph to discuss his new book, "
        },
        {
          "text": "The Third Reconstruction",
          "italic": true
        },
        {
          "text": ", and his interpretations of American history."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Zachary sets the scene with his poem entitled, “The Third Reconstruction.”"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Peniel E. Joseph  is the Barbara Jordan Chair in Ethics and Political Values, Founding Director of the Center for the Study of Race and Democracy, and Associate Dean for Justice, Equity, Diversity, and Inclusion at the LBJ School of Public Affairs and Professor of History at the University of Texas at Austin. He is the author of award-winning books on African American history, including "
        },
        {
          "text": "The Sword and the Shield, Stokely: A Life, ",
          "italic": true
        },
        {
          "text": "and most recently, "
        },
        {
          "text": "The Third Reconstruction",
          "italic": true
        },
        {
          "text": "."
